Boil a full #kettle{}, then pour the boiled water into a #saucepan{} with
@salt{1/2%tsp} on high heat.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, add the @sliced mushrooms{120%g} to the pan. Season with @salt{to taste}
and @pepper{to taste} and fry, stirring occasionally, until browned,
~{5-6%minutes}.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).

Add the @gochujang paste{30%g} (add less if you'd prefer things milder) and
garlic to the mushrooms. Stir-fry for ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in the @vegetable stock paste{10%g} and @water{100%ml} (for the sauce).

Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer until the liquid has reduced
slightly, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Meanwhile, add the @spinach and ricotta ravioli{250%g} to your pan of boiling water
and bring back to the boil.

Cook until tender, ~{3%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop back in the pan. Drizzle with
@oil{drizzle} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Once the sauce has reduced, stir the @creme fraiche{75%g}, @butter{20%g} and
half the @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%g} into the pan.

Simmer for ~{1%minute}. Add a splash of @water{splash} if it's a little too thick,
then remove from the heat.

Taste and season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste} if needed.

Add the cooked ravioli to the sauce and stir gently to combine.

Share the ravioli between your #bowls{} and sprinkle over the remaining hard Italian
style cheese.

Garnish with the @crispy onions{1%sachet}.

Serve the @wild rocket{20%g} on the side with a drizzle of @olive oil{drizzle}.
Enjoy!